  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose is provide equal, accessible, inclusive education services to visually impaired school age children thereby promoting access to mainstream services within their communities.

The programme targets to enable at least 50% of visually impaired children in the project area access to inclusive educational services.

The main activities of the programme include programme Management, Vision screening, Advocacy, Human Resource development, environmental modification, provision of learning aids and teaching. 

The project aims at contributing towards making education accessible to all school age children</narrative>
  </description>
